            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-69651",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2025-69651"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://scout.docker.com/v/CVE-2025-69651?s=debian&n=binutils&ns=debian&t=deb&osn=debian&osv=13&vr=%3C%3D2.44-3",
              "help": {
                "text": "GNU Binutils thru 2.46 readelf contains a vulnerability that leads to an invalid pointer free when processing a crafted ELF binary with malformed relocation or symbol data. If dump_relocations returns early due to parsing errors, the internal all_relocations array may remain partially uninitialized. Later, process_got_section_contents() may attempt to free an invalid r_symbol pointer, triggering memory corruption checks in glibc and causing the program to terminate with SIGABRT. No evidence of further memory corruption or code execution was observed; the impact is limited to denial of service. NOTE: this is disputed by third parties because the observed behavior occurred only in pre-release code and did not affect any tagged version.\n\n---\n- binutils <unfixed> (unimportant)\nhttps://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33700\nhttps://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=ea4bc025abdba85a90e26e13f551c16a44bfa921\nbinutils not covered by security support\n",
                "markdown": "> GNU Binutils thru 2.46 readelf contains a vulnerability that leads to an invalid pointer free when processing a crafted ELF binary with malformed relocation or symbol data. If dump_relocations returns early due to parsing errors, the internal all_relocations array may remain partially uninitialized. Later, process_got_section_contents() may attempt to free an invalid r_symbol pointer, triggering memory corruption checks in glibc and causing the program to terminate with SIGABRT. No evidence of further memory corruption or code execution was observed; the impact is limited to denial of service. NOTE: this is disputed by third parties because the observed behavior occurred only in pre-release code and did not affect any tagged version.\n\n---\n- binutils <unfixed> (unimportant)\nhttps://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33700\nhttps://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=ea4bc025abdba85a90e26e13f551c16a44bfa921\nbinutils not covered by security support\n\n|                                                                                              |\n|Package         pkg:deb/debian/binutils@2.44-3?os_distro=trixie&os_name=debian&os_version=13  |\n|Affected range  <=2.44-3                                                                      |\n|Fixed version   not fixed                                                                     |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "affected_version": "<=2.44-3",
                "cvssV3_severity": "LOW",
                "fixed_version": "not fixed",
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/binutils@2.44-3?os_distro=trixie&os_name=debian&os_version=13"
                ],
                "security-severity": "3.1",
                "tags": [
